<title>USA: Quixote authorizes share buyback.</title>
<headline>Quixote authorizes share buyback.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-04-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Quixote Corp said Monday its board had authorized the repurchase of up to one million shares of its common stock.</p>
<p>The shares may be purchased from time to time in open market transactions, the company said. There are currently eight million Quixote shares outstanding.</p>
<p>&quot;Our buyback program is reflective of the confidence we have in our future,&quot; Chairman Philip Rollhaus said in a statement.</p>
<p>Quixote provides highway and truck-mounted impact attenuators and related highway safety products.</p>
<p>((--Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787))</p>
